    "To the best of our knowledge, the levels in Bloom's taxonomy at which GPT-4 commits cognitive errors have not yet been elucidated.",
    "Thus, we performed a detailed assessment of the answers and reasoning provided by GPT-4.In our analysis, we found that most errors were made at the lowest level of Bloom's taxonomy, labeled \"remember.\"",
    "In these answers, GPT-4 failed at naming or using a specific fact, as evident in the text response.",
    "In the example presented in the previous section, GPT-4 named most of the diagnostic criteria for a somatization disorder but did not mention the time criterion.",
    "In this context, it is important to note that GPT-4 has been trained with publicly available and licensed data (although these are not specified in detail by OpenAI) [32]."
